<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>  
  
 <hibernate-mapping>  
  <class name="Employee" table="Emp">  
    
     <id name="empid">  
     <generator class="assigned"></generator>  
     </id>  
            
    <property name="empname"></property>  
    <property name="addr"></property>  
            
  </class>         
 </hibernate-mapping>

- This is a traditional process by which we can save the data. But everytime writing the mapping file is difficult. It may be error prone as we writing lot of xml code.

- The below configuration we need to use in hibernate.cfg.xml file.

   <!-- List of XML mapping files -->
   <mapping resource="Employee.hbm.xml"/>